comments: Brogdon (POR) delivers his forearm into Dinwiddie's (BKN) side, which affects his body's trajectory and driving shot attempt.
Grant (POR) places his hands to Dinwiddie's (BKN) body and then releases as he sets the pick.
Claxton (BKN) briefly grasps Reath's (POR) jersey during the screen, which he immediately removes and does not affect Reath's FOM.
Bridges (BKN) retreats in Brogdon's (POR) path when he absorbs the body contact that occurs.
Bridges (BKN) gives Simons (POR) a step of distance when he stops in his path and absorbs the incoming contact during the pick.
Bridges (BKN) engages and disengages with Simons (POR) as he attempts to establish a position in the post.

Dinwiddie (BKN) releases from Grant (POR) as his forearm comes out slightly at the end of the drive, and the contact that occurs is marginal before Grant makes incidental leg contact with Walker (POR) causing him to trip.
Brogdon (POR) maintains his pivot foot prior to releasing his pass.
Bridges (BKN) brushes Simons' (POR) lower body with his leg as he starts his upward shooting motion, which does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Walker (POR) moves and jumps alongside Bridges' (BKN) path toward the basket when marginal contact occurs on the driving shot attempt.

After Bridges (BKN) cleanly blocks the shot, Finney-Smith (BKN) is also reaching for the ball when marginal contact occurs with the top of Camara's (POR) head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
O'Neale (BKN) releases the inbounds pass within five seconds.
Brogdon (POR) briefly places his hand on Dinwiddie's (BKN) side and immediately removes it prior to the release of the inbounds pass.

Grant (POR) jumps alongside Johnson (BKN) and toward the basket when he legally contests the driving shot attempt. The lower body contact is initiated by Johnson who has his leg extended backward during the release.
Bridges (BKN) slides his hand off Simons' (POR) arm during the drive, and Simons can move through the contact.
Both Reath (POR) and Johnson (BKN) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
